		"description": "<p>At 13th level, you can walk through locked doors almost without breaking stride and can unweave magical effects with your tools alone. As a bonus action, you can automatically succeed on any thieves’ tools check with a DC of 10 + your Dexterity bonus + your Proficiency bonus or less.</p>\n<p>You can also attempt to dispel permanent magical effects with your thieves’ tools. Doing so requires a Sleight of Hand check against the spell’s spell save DC (use the spellcaster’s save DC if the spell doesn’t usually require a saving throw) and 10 minutes. If you succeed, the magical effect is dispelled. If you fail, it is immediately cast on you (if applicable) or you take a number of d6s of force damage equal to the spell level which cannot be prevented in any way.</p>",
